# Ignore patterns for `tauri dev`'s file watcher.
#
# Tauri 2 watches the entire cargo workspace by default and rebuilds on
# any file change. macOS Finder writes `.DS_Store` whenever a folder is
# accessed (including by `cargo` traversing build artefacts), which the
# default watcher treats as a source-change → triggers a rebuild loop.
#
# We also exclude `target/` directories because rebuild artefacts are
# obviously not source. The `plugins-ext/` workspace is a separate cargo
# workspace (excluded from the host's `[workspace]`), and IronRDP is a
# git submodule whose own `target/` shouldn't trigger anything either.

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Build artefacts (host + every nested workspace)
target/
**/target/

# Submodule + sibling workspaces — we depend on them as path/git deps,
# not as live source.
plugins-ext/
IronRDP/

# Generated docs / dist trees
docs/_build/
gui/dist/
